oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Crayon print of Pvt. Henry R. Hubbs
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Pvt. Henry R. Hubbs, a box maker from Knoxville, served in Co. E, 130th Inf. Regt., 33rd Div. In this studio portrait, Hubbs is seated beside a table with wine and a glass. It says "Souvenir of Luxemburg." Pvt. Hubbs trained at Camp Gordon, Georgia and was overseas from August 26, 1918 until May 20, 1919.
